<br>
IMHO, folks under 55 are usually more hindrance than help in sky.  If I was running a sky raid, I'd draw the line at 55.  I would accept clerics under 55 if we were short on CH'ers, though.  CH will be needed for a few of the boss critters later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bippinfv>bippinfv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf-hugger</span><br>  Posts: 1193<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/25/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For sky, the ideal is about ..</span><hr size=1> *laugh Bjond*<br>
Oh, I do hope Valquiss will come and post here.<br>
Bjond, I do value your experience and knowledge, but that's not quite the case. The fellowship had a series of raids into Sky, learning the place, and I think we had one over 55 person at the time - a ranger of 58+ to tank (either Molsone or Iuliane, both were there on different occasions). Eventually we had a few more, as this took place over months, but we did decently even below that. Granted, we only made it to the Keeper of Souls isle, but it was still pretty good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Had several paladin and ranger epics as a result. Oh, and monk <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
We did that with one cleric some times too. And I don't think we ever had more than 24 people. <br>
So don't succomb to accepted limitations. Test yourself, be creative, and have fun, it's a very interesting place. I'll be happy to help with advice, or participation if I can. I enjoyed sky very much.<br>
As for a multi day raid, you can leave keys on corpses up there, and summon the raid back to an advanced island, on another day, if you're willing to spring for the coffins.<br>
