<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561580" target="top">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=561580</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirdo>Sirdo</A> at: 3/26/03 5:51:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2290<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/03 4:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eh, Bip ..</span><hr size=1> .. I did not mean to imply that it was impossible for under 55 to do sky.  Of course it's possible.  I spent FAR too much time in sky back when the zone was just added.  That was pre-kunark with not one person over level 50 or in anything but what would be considered poor gear on a level 20 player today -- well, some had vox/naggy/fear gear, but nothing from kunark or later.<br>
<br>
I just personally would not want to do an open sky raid with anyone but a few key non-fighting types under 55.  A guild or aliance raid with under 55?  NP, let's go for it.  Open?  No way.  Due to the mechanics of the zone, a sky raid requires the one thing typically in shortest supply on open raids.  No, that's not talent or experience.  It's commitment to seeing the raid reach it's goal.  People bail out on open raids all the time for trivial reasons.  That means that if you do it with an open raid, it behooves you to be overpowered or you'll have to abort when people start to bail out.  Remember, there is no loot in sky for anyone but the people getting epics -- not much incentive for an open raid to keep focused.<br>
<br>
BTW, the monk epic part for sky takes 3-4 people tops.  I would not do it as part of a sky raid unless you plan on killing Djorn, too, for some strange reason.  The entire last four fights for monk epic are all single-group fights that would be a waste of time to a raid force.  I help people do epics and such all the time -- I'm all for helping folks out.  I just don't like to see 20-30 people's time wasted.  Raid time is for things that require a raid.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if I was to do it with an under 55 team, I'd require everyone to be ready for 8+ solid hours of raiding.  No gating out early.  No whining about too many deaths, etc. etc..  Everyone needs to be truly comitted or you risk having to cancel it midstride when your only necro decides it's time to sleep or you start suffering from cleric attrition or .. whatever.<br>
<br>
Oh, eh, I wish y'all lots of luck and plenty of success, but it will likely be from a distance.  Sky is by far my least favorite zone to raid.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thewthunderstrike>ThewThunderstrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/03 11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> When you have a date and time...</span><hr size=1> When you have a date and time, post it.  <br>
